Function: noun
Inflected Form: -s
Etymology: Portuguese araribá, from Tupi
1 : any of several trees of the genus Centrolobium (family Leguminosae); especially : a Brazilian tree (C. robustum) -- called also zebrawood
2 : any of several trees of the genus Sickingia usually with heavy dark red wood
3 : the wood of an arariba tree
